Source:  Our Street
Author:  SUTTON-SMITH
Vol / Page:  17
Edition:
Quote:  "You went for the messages this morning." <i>Ibid.</i> 33 Most Saturday morning after messages had been done and bagzing for the afternoon on Gormie's porch was over, Brin and Smitty and Horsey and Gormie would go along to the park to have some kicks.
Notes:  1975 edition

Date:  1/12/1957
Source:  Personal Communication
Author:  W.J. JIMPSON
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  The following I have noted since I came to New Zealand ... Messages: to us [British], this always implies carrying information and our term for small shopping is `errands'.
Notes:  1957 Dec 1 p.c. W.J. Jimpson (Tolaga Bay)

